This paper proposes a new CNN-LSTM model for recognizing surgical tasks in robotic-assisted radical prostatectomies. The focus is on evaluating the model's performance using task-based efficiency metrics, which suggests a focus on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of system events, which suggests a potential focus on robotics (RO). Additionally, the proposed approach could have applications in artificial intelligence (AI) and human-computer interaction (HC) for improving surgeon training and patient care. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.RO, followed by cs.AI and cs.HC.
